The Situation Room
Live from Washington
Wednesday, April 11, 2007

IN THE NEWS:
•	North Carolina: 3 Duke Lacrosse Players are “Innocent”
•	Defense Secretary Gates Orders 15-month Tours for Army in Iraq
•	Air Traffic Controller Needed a Bathroom Break.  So 2 flights Held Up

IN POLITICS:
•	Sen. McCain: Democrats Accepting Defeat in Iraq
•	Fred Thompson’s Cancer Slow-Growing, in Remission: Doctor


IN THE CAFFERTY FILE:
•	Can the military continue to do what it’s being asked to do indefinitely without a draft?
•	What does it mean if the White House can't find anyone willing to take the job of “war czar”?
•	Should House Speaker Nancy Pelosi take a diplomatic trip to Iran?

